The paper focuses on the problem of saliency detection using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the transformation of the network's deeper layers, which is related to the field of neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper examines the properties of the learnt representation, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses visualization techniques to analyze the network's receptive fields, which is a common approach in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV).
